    "description": "Fibromuscular dysplasia (FMD) is a rare vascular disorder that affects the blood vessels, particularly the carotid and renal arteries, leading to abnormal growth of the cells in the vessel walls. This condition can result in stenosis (narrowing), aneurysm formation, or dissection, and is often asymptomatic, detected incidentally during imaging for other conditions. It predominantly affects women and can lead to serious complications such as stroke or hypertension if left untreated.",
    "symptoms": [
      {
