        "symptom": "Vision changes",
        "description": "Experiencing blurred vision or transient vision loss due to vascular involvement in the neck."
      },
      {
        "symptom": "Abdominal pain",
        "description": "Pain in the abdomen, which can be related to renal artery involvement and compromised blood flow."
      }
    ],
    "treatments": "Treatment for fibromuscular dysplasia is tailored to the individual's symptoms and severity of the condition. For hypertension, medications such as angiotensin-converting enzyme (ACE) inhibitors or calcium channel blockers are commonly prescribed. In cases where stenosis is severe, angioplasty with or without stenting may be indicated to open the affected artery. Surgical intervention may be necessary for complications such as aneurysms or dissections. Regular follow-up with imaging studies is crucial to monitor disease progression and cardiovascular health."
